        <Parent_String>Crocodilia (order) [300310265], Reptilia (class) [300265956], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a family containing two living genera and 23 living species of large, amphibious, carnivorous reptiles having powerful jaws, short legs with clawed, webbed toes, a body form that allows the eyes, ears, and nostrils to be above the water surface while most of the animal is hidden below, a long massive tail, and thick, plated skin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047484/Animal Diversity Web (1995-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>含兩個現存的屬以及二十三種大型肉食性兩棲爬蟲動物。牠們的顎強而有力，腿短有爪，指間有蹼；由於體型的緣故，牠們在大部份身體藏於水中時，仍露出眼睛、耳朵以及鼻孔。尾巴長而粗大，皮膚厚且覆蓋著鱗甲。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Orden de reptiles acuáticos o anfibios con cuerpo y cola robustos, extremidades cortas y robustas, un fuerte cráneo aplanado y alargado con orificios nasales en la punta del hocico y un paladar secundario bien desarrollado. Desde el Paleoceno hasta el presente, incluyendo tres familias vivas, ocho géneros y 23 especies de cocodrilos, gaviales, caimanes y caimanes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tecuanimeh tlen nemih pan atl ica inintlacayo huan inincuitlapil chicahuac huan cacaltic, ininicxi cototzitzin huan chihchicauhtic, chicactic inintzonceton  patlachtic huan cuahuehueyactizn ica iyacatzol eltoc itlamiyan icamac huan ica ce achi tlen inenepil tlen huahcapan tlen tlahuel cualli  eltoc. Ipan Paleoceno azta naman, calaqui eyi tlamanti familias tlen yoltoqueh, chicueyi generos huan cempohualli huan eyi tlamantli acquetzpalli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
